ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: I have been treated as less competent by others when they learned about my suicidal thoughts or behavior.
Notes: 0= Never; 1= Seldom; 2= Sometimes; 3= Often; 4= Very often

ElementDescription: I have been shunned or avoided when others found out about my suicidal thoughts or behavior.
Notes: 0= Never; 1= Seldom; 2= Sometimes; 3= Often; 4= Very often

ElementDescription: Some people think that because of my suicidal thoughts or behavior I will never be normal again.
Notes: 0= Never; 1= Seldom; 2= Sometimes; 3= Often; 4= Very often

ElementDescription: My suicidal thoughts or behavior has led to some people treating me badly.
Notes: 0= Never; 1= Seldom; 2= Sometimes; 3= Often; 4= Very often

Notes: 0= Never; 1= Seldom; 2= Sometimes; 3= Often; 4= Very often

ElementDescription: Personal Suicide Stigma Questionnaire - Rejection Subscore
Notes: Sum of items pssq_rejection1-4, 6

ElementDescription: Personal Suicide Stigma Questionnaire - Minimization Subscore
Notes: Sum of items pssq_minimization5, 7-9

ElementDescription: Personal Suicide Stigma Questionnaire - Self-Blame
Notes: Sum of items pssq_selfblame10-16
